{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C3018 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C3018 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"pos":[618,638],"content":"Compiler Error C3018","linkify":"Compiler Error C3018","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C3018","pos":[0,20]}]},{"content":"'var1' : OpenMP 'for' test or increment must use index variable 'var2'","pos":[639,709]},{"pos":[716,831],"content":"A <ph id=\"ph1\">`for`</ph> loop in an OpenMP statement must use the same variable for its test and increment as it uses for its index.","source":"A `for` loop in an OpenMP statement must use the same variable for its test and increment as it uses for its index."},{"content":"The following sample generates C3018:","pos":[838,875]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C3018 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-csharp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"article\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C3018\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C3018\"\nms.assetid: 685be45f-f116-43a8-a88d-05ab6616e2f1\ncaps.latest.revision: 7\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\ntranslation.priority.mt: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C3018\n'var1' : OpenMP 'for' test or increment must use index variable 'var2'  \n  \n A `for` loop in an OpenMP statement must use the same variable for its test and increment as it uses for its index.  \n  \n The following sample generates C3018:  \n  \n```  \n// C3018.cpp  \n// compile with: /openmp  \nint main()  \n{  \n   int i = 0, j = 5;  \n  \n   #pragma omp parallel  \n   {  \n      #pragma omp for  \n      for (i = 0; j < 10; ++i)   // C3018  \n      // try the the following line instead  \n      // for (i = 0; i < 10; ++i)  \n         j *= 2;  \n  \n      #pragma omp for  \n      for (i = 0; i < 10; j = j + i)   // C3018  \n      // try the the following line instead  \n      // for (i = 0; i < 10; i = j + i)  \n         j *= 2;  \n   }  \n}  \n```"}